  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently in aggressive gamma hedging mode as SPX sits just below the 6577 flip strike, with spot at 6571.69 triggering buying pressure as they hedge their long gamma position. The massive 32.4% and 118.6% GEX surges indicate heavy option flow concentration, creating a powerful stabilizing force with the 6575-6580 gamma wall acting as immediate resistance where dealers will sell any rally attempts.\n\nExpect choppy, range-bound action between 6570 support (dealers buy) and 6580 resistance (dealers sell) as the PIN regime favors mean reversion - any break above 6580 faces the largest gamma wall at 93.4B, while a drop toward 6550 (-22.4B negative gamma) would flip dealers to momentum sellers and accelerate downside.\n\n**Key levels: Watch 6577 flip strike for regime change, 6580 for heavy dealer selling, and 6550 breakdown for gamma flip acceleration.**",
